column18:
We are currently recruiting participants for a study aimed at better understanding how teachers leverage online tools to inform their instruction. 
Teachers selected to participate will be asked to complete two short surveys each week over four weeks (eight surveys total), and may be asked to record a short video reflection.  The surveys will take less than 3 minutes to complete and will focus on what social networks and other online resources teachers use to help them teach. 
Participants will receive a $50 Amazon gift card for their participation. If interested, please complete the following recruitment form, and feel free to share it with your colleagues. 
Thank you for your interest in our study. If you have questions about this study, please contact:

Stephen J. Aguilar, Ph.D.                 
3470 Trousdale Parkway 
Los Angeles, CA 90089
aguilars@usc.edu                                            

The University of Southern California's Institutional Review Board Health Sciences and Behavioral Sciences has determined that this study is exempt from IRB oversight.
